<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="509" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1370,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1370,1396]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1818" box="[286,375,1370,1396]" class="Polychaeta" family="Amphinomidae" genus="Chloeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphinomida" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[286,375,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">Chloeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with ventral cirri of similar size throughout body; bipinnate branchiae from chaetiger 4; middorsal spots with a median constriction, surrounded by a circular pale area over a darker background, projected as lateral bands; chaetal bundles homogeneously pale.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="509" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1370,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1479,1505]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">Remarks.</emphasis>
No specimens were studied; Horst 
<typeStatus box="[727,775,1479,1505]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">type</typeStatus>
specimens are deposited in Leiden, but this 
<typeStatus box="[1290,1338,1479,1505]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">type</typeStatus>
was not listed in the corresponding catalogue (
<bibRefCitation author="Bleeker, J. &amp; van der Spoel, S." box="[583,933,1514,1541]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" pagination="121 - 166" refId="ref21631" refString="Bleeker, J. &amp; van der Spoel, S. (1992) Catalogue of the Polychaeta collected by the Siboga Expedition and type specimens of Polychaeta in the Zoological Museum of Amsterdam. Bulletin Zoologischen Museum, Universiteit van Amsterdam, 13, 121 - 166." type="journal article" year="1992">Bleeker &amp; van der Spoel 1992</bibRefCitation>
). However, the original description provides complete details and illustration of the pigmentation pattern, which resembles a horseshoe with a middorsal line medially constricted on each segment. No specimens from tropical American seas show this pigmentation pattern. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Fauvel, P." box="[269,462,1622,1649]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref23004" refString="Fauvel, P. (1943) Annelides polychetes de Californie recueillies par L. Diguet. Memoires du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 18, 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1943">Fauvel (1943: 7)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Horst" authorityYear="1910" box="[579,728,1623,1649]" class="Polychaeta" family="Amphinomidae" genus="Chloeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphinomida" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="conspicua">
<emphasis box="[579,728,1623,1649]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">C. conspicua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the Gulf of 
<collectingRegion box="[918,1032,1622,1648]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">California</collectingRegion>
and he indicated that (transl.) “the dorsal surface has two thin longitudinal pale bands separating three other wider, brown reddish bands, that are modified in each segment into a slightly wider medial band ahead of two slightly oblique lateral bands, and more or less fused basally below the median band. This outlook is very similar to the dorsal pattern of a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1818" box="[1200,1289,1730,1756]" class="Polychaeta" family="Amphinomidae" genus="Chloeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphinomida" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1200,1289,1730,1756]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">Chloeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Taboga illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Monro, C. C. A." box="[309,492,1767,1793]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" pagination="1 - 96" refId="ref24599" refString="Monro, C. C. A. (1933) The Polychaeta Errantia collected by Dr. C. Crossland at Colon, in the Panama Region, and the Galapagos Islands during the Expedition of the S. Y. ' St. George'. Proceedings of the General Meetings for Scientific Business of the Zoological Society of London, 1933 (1), 1 - 96. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1933. tb 01578. x" type="journal article" year="1933">Monro (1933: 9</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[505,576,1766,1793]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1669,1693]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,183,1645]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1436,181,1645]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chloeia euglochis Ehlers, 1887, reinstated. A. Syntype complete (MCZ ANNa-720), dorsal view. B. Same, illustration from Ehlers (1887). C. Same, extract from Haeckel’s plates (1904, Pl. 96). D. Another syntype (MCZ ANNa-3), oblique lateral view. E. Notochaeta. F, G. Neurochaetae (from Ehlers 1887) (Photo: D, Elizabeth Borda)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479997" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479997/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
)”. As indicated below, Monro’s record corresponds with 
<taxonomicName authority="Augener, 1922" authorityName="Augener" authorityYear="1922" class="Polychaeta" family="Amphinomidae" genus="Chloeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphinomida" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pseudeuglochis">
<emphasis box="[1229,1437,1766,1793]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">C. pseudeuglochis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Augener, H." box="[151,319,1803,1829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" pagination="38 - 53" refId="ref21238" refString="Augener, H. (1922) Ueber litorale Polychaeten von Westindien. Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschender Freunde zu Berlin, 1922 (3 - 5), 38 - 53." type="journal article" year="1922">Augener, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and Fauvel’s record is listed under that species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="509" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1370,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1838,1864]" pageId="6" pageNumber="509">Distribution</emphasis>
. The species was described with specimens from Sumatra and Java in the Western Pacific, in shallow water (
<quantity box="[323,409,1875,1901]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="509" unit="m" value="6.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="1.0">1–12 m</quantity>
depth).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
